03:33.630 --> 03:34.630
[meows]

04:18.009 --> 04:19.135
Hi.

04:20.343 --> 04:21.511
I finished your book.

04:23.181 --> 04:24.639
I finished your book.

04:24.723 --> 04:26.100
You don't have to sign.

04:26.184 --> 04:27.476
I know you can read my lips,

04:27.559 --> 04:28.936
but I am getting better.

04:29.020 --> 04:30.020
Better.

04:30.772 --> 04:32.689
- I um... I want to practise.
- Cool.

04:33.440 --> 04:36.235
Taking another class with John.

04:36.318 --> 04:37.486
- John?
- It's fun!

04:38.196 --> 04:41.908
I am way better at understanding it
than actually doing it, but...

04:43.034 --> 04:44.786
So, what did you think?

04:44.869 --> 04:46.954
What did I... What did I think?

04:48.747 --> 04:50.249
- I loved it.
- Thank you.

04:50.332 --> 04:51.332
I um...

04:52.126 --> 04:54.461
I loved Riley.

04:54.544 --> 04:55.963
I loved Erin.

04:56.047 --> 04:58.465
- Thank you.
- They were great characters.

04:59.258 --> 05:02.552
I tried to guess the ending.

05:03.095 --> 05:07.225
I am usually on point with that
sort of thing, but I was way off!

05:07.975 --> 05:09.768
How did you do that?
How do you...?

05:09.852 --> 05:11.520
How do you come up with that?

05:12.104 --> 05:15.565
My mom calls it "writer brain."

05:15.649 --> 05:16.775
Makes me crazy.

05:17.317 --> 05:21.823
Any possible outcome
is like a movie in my head...

05:21.906 --> 05:23.615
with many endings.

05:23.698 --> 05:26.493
- A frustrating movie.
- [laughs]

05:27.161 --> 05:30.330
Hard to make the voices quiet.

05:32.208 --> 05:33.251
A voice?

05:34.168 --> 05:35.377
I have a voice in my mind.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.966
Does the voice sound like a kid?

05:41.926 --> 05:43.552
You were 13 when you got sick?

05:45.428 --> 05:47.556
It sounds like my mom.

05:50.433 --> 05:53.855
Whatever is going on in your brain,

05:53.938 --> 05:58.234
I think that you are a good storyteller.

06:01.320 --> 06:02.320
What?

06:06.449 --> 06:08.035
This means...

06:08.119 --> 06:09.828
kisser.

06:09.912 --> 06:10.912
[laughs]

06:10.955 --> 06:12.957
This means storyteller.

06:14.208 --> 06:16.418
Well,
I'm sure you're also a lovely kisser.

06:17.377 --> 06:18.378
[alarm blares]

06:29.514 --> 06:30.514
[sound fades out]

06:33.435 --> 06:34.896
[sound fades in, alarm blares]

06:37.064 --> 06:38.065
[meows]

06:44.196 --> 06:45.196
[alarm stops]

06:49.201 --> 06:50.244
Jesus!

06:54.789 --> 06:56.208
I'm sorry.

06:56.292 --> 06:58.585
Fire alarm.

06:58.668 --> 07:02.672
God! That is one hell of a fire alarm!

07:02.756 --> 07:05.176
I have to feel the vibrations.

07:05.259 --> 07:07.053
That is why it is so loud.

07:07.136 --> 07:09.013
When I am sleeping,

07:09.096 --> 07:11.057
the vibrations will wake me up.

07:11.140 --> 07:13.100
Well, I imagine that would wake anyone.

07:20.857 --> 07:21.858
Oh! Cat?

07:22.567 --> 07:24.778
She is fine. Independent little bitch.

07:25.947 --> 07:27.656
She's a... She's a what?

07:28.240 --> 07:31.743
B-I-T-C-H.

07:31.826 --> 07:32.826
[laughs]

07:33.870 --> 07:34.704
Bitch.

07:34.788 --> 07:35.872
Bitch.

07:42.504 --> 07:43.504
[pats leg]

07:43.546 --> 07:44.798
I am sorry about dinner.

07:46.342 --> 07:47.509
Do you want to come over?

07:48.219 --> 07:50.470
We can order in and watch a movie.

07:50.553 --> 07:52.597
John will be home in an hour,
so he can join.

07:52.681 --> 07:54.808
Have to work.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.019
I understand.

07:57.103 --> 07:58.103
I'm sorry.

07:58.770 --> 08:02.482
Thank you for...
for letting me borrow this.

08:02.565 --> 08:04.443
Keep it. I have got dozens upstairs.

08:05.902 --> 08:06.903
Thank you.

08:08.406 --> 08:10.740
I'll pop by tomorrow and brush up signs?

08:11.574 --> 08:12.826
I'm going to get good.

08:12.909 --> 08:13.910
I'm determined.

08:15.287 --> 08:16.746
- Kissing.
- Kissing.

08:16.830 --> 08:17.914
Storyteller.

08:18.915 --> 08:19.916
Bitch.

08:20.001 --> 08:21.002
Bitch.

08:31.220 --> 08:32.554
[message tone, vibrating]

08:53.533 --> 08:54.533
[sighs]

09:39.163 --> 09:40.163
[sighs]

09:46.920 --> 09:48.797
[female voice] <i>...clenching the book</i>

09:48.880 --> 09:50.590
<i>Riley to the church.</i>

09:50.673 --> 09:51.758
<i>The church to Erin.</i>

09:52.717 --> 09:54.095
<i>The church to Father Paul.</i>

09:54.178 --> 09:56.012
<i>Bring in Erin. Scratch that. Try this.</i>

09:56.097 --> 09:58.182
<i>The rage bubbled up,
spreading into his head.</i>

09:58.265 --> 09:59.808
<i>His ears rang. His eyes felt hot.</i>

09:59.891 --> 10:00.725
<i>She's happy.</i>

10:00.809 --> 10:02.478
<i>...mysterious ways.</i>

10:02.561 --> 10:04.271
<i>Nope, not working.</i>

10:04.355 --> 10:06.940
<i>Not working. Something brighter.</i>

10:08.150 --> 10:11.195
<i>...looking down with her wide,
endlessly patient eyes.</i>

10:11.278 --> 10:13.738
<i>They would twinkle with red,
blue and yellow light,</i>

10:13.822 --> 10:15.491
<i>just as the damned Jesus fish had</i>

10:15.574 --> 10:17.909
<i>when it pulled him out of the fog
and into hell.</i>

10:17.992 --> 10:18.827
<i>That's better.</i>

10:18.910 --> 10:21.037
<i>It needs something more, something better.</i>

10:21.122 --> 10:24.958
<i>Erin dies. Can't kill Erin. That would
piss 'em off. Didn't set it up properly.</i>

10:25.041 --> 10:27.419
<i>Or scrap the whole book
and find another career.</i>

10:27.503 --> 10:28.628
<i>A better idea.</i>

10:28.711 --> 10:30.131
[voice fades out]

10:38.222 --> 10:39.222
[sighs]

10:47.981 --> 10:48.982
[ringing]

10:57.283 --> 10:58.284
[ringing]

11:09.545 --> 11:10.546
[sighs]

11:21.097 --> 11:22.097
[ringing]

11:24.100 --> 11:25.685
[phone continues ringing]

11:35.446 --> 11:36.447
[ringing stops]

12:07.269 --> 12:08.728
[screams] Maddie!

12:09.396 --> 12:11.147
Maddie, please see me!

12:11.232 --> 12:12.065
[pounds on door]

12:12.148 --> 12:14.276
Maddie, please help me!

12:14.360 --> 12:15.361
[sound fades out]

12:20.949 --> 12:22.409
Maddie! [cries out]

12:23.910 --> 12:25.371
[cries out]

12:27.414 --> 12:29.375
[cries out]

12:30.251 --> 12:31.251
No!

12:32.670 --> 12:34.003
No!

12:34.837 --> 12:36.465
[yells] No!

12:36.548 --> 12:37.548
[gasps]

12:42.929 --> 12:43.929
[cries out]

12:50.396 --> 12:51.396
[cries out]

12:58.861 --> 13:00.071
[door rattles]

13:59.381 --> 14:00.758
[phone ringing, vibrating]

14:21.445 --> 14:22.446
[ringing stops]

14:30.621 --> 14:31.789
[door opening, typing]

14:49.263 --> 14:51.600
[knife blade tapping]

14:56.104 --> 14:57.648
[tapping continues]

15:05.363 --> 15:06.657
[ringing]

15:10.577 --> 15:11.577
<i>Hey, Squish.</i>

15:11.620 --> 15:12.830
Hey, Squash.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.288
<i>What are you up to?</i>

15:14.372 --> 15:15.707
Abandoning the novel.

15:15.791 --> 15:17.125
Joining the circus.

15:17.208 --> 15:18.794
<i>Going that well, huh?</i>

15:20.920 --> 15:21.755
[Max laughs]

15:21.839 --> 15:23.214
<i>Are you still stuck on the ending?</i>

15:23.297 --> 15:25.884
Which one? I have seven.

15:26.885 --> 15:28.804
<i>Glad I could distract you.</i>

15:28.887 --> 15:30.388
Distractions abound.

15:31.139 --> 15:33.266
Craig texted me.

15:33.349 --> 15:35.686
<i>Talk about bad endings!
Did you talk to him?</i>

15:36.520 --> 15:38.605
No, but almost.

15:38.689 --> 15:39.857
<i>It's been a year!</i>

15:39.939 --> 15:42.108
<i>Mom keeps asking
when you're getting back out there.</i>

15:43.359 --> 15:46.738
I signed up for an online-dating site
for the Deaf.

15:47.321 --> 15:48.321
<i>Look at you!</i>

15:48.364 --> 15:51.785
No. There are four men in the whole area.

15:51.869 --> 15:53.912
Do not want.

15:54.621 --> 15:55.997
<i>Miss the city yet?</i>

15:56.080 --> 15:57.916
Never. Too loud.

15:57.999 --> 15:59.292
<i>Seriously, Maddie?</i>

15:59.375 --> 16:01.043
<i>Maybe you could come back.</i>

16:01.127 --> 16:02.378
<i>Live with me.</i>

16:02.463 --> 16:04.213
<i>I worry about you.</i>

16:04.297 --> 16:07.341
<i>It is not good for anyone to be alone,
Squish.</i>

16:07.425 --> 16:10.929
<i>- Isolating yourself the way that you do...</i>
- Isolation happened to me.

16:11.012 --> 16:12.598
I didn't pick it.

16:14.683 --> 16:15.684
<i>Who was that?</i>

16:17.351 --> 16:20.062
<i>Behind you.
I thought I saw something move.</i>

16:22.023 --> 16:23.274
Probably the cat.

16:23.357 --> 16:24.610
Bitch escaped earlier.

16:24.693 --> 16:27.738
Thank you. I have to find her.

16:28.489 --> 16:29.363
<i>I love you.</i>

16:29.447 --> 16:30.447
I love you.

16:49.676 --> 16:50.677
[rattling]

17:15.536 --> 17:16.537
[cat food rattling]

17:28.715 --> 17:29.716
[sighs]

17:38.140 --> 17:39.141
[cat food rattling]

